Assets account-debit increase(s) and credit
decrease(s)
Liability accounts -credit increase(s) and debit
decrease(s)
Expenses account-debit increase(s) and credit
decrease
• Revenue accounts -credit increase(s) and debit
decrease(s)
• Capital accounts-credit (s) and debit decrease(s)
Balancing a ledger account
The teacher should guide the learner in describing the
procedure of balancing of the ledger accounts and explaining
its importance.
Balancing off a ledger account
The teacher should assist the leaner in balancing off a ledger
account, emphasizing on the terms balance carried down
(bal%) and balance brought down (bal/d).
Posting transactions in various ledger accounts as
shown
Assets/Expenses account
Cr
The trial balance
The teacher should lead the leaner in:
• explaining the terin trial balance'.
A trial balance is a statement prepared at a particular
date showing all the debit balances on one column and
all the credit balances on the other column.
NB Emphasize that the trial balance is extracted from the
balances of the ledger accounts.
• Transferring the balances from the ledger account to
the trial balance.
Increases
Decreases
Capital Liabilities/Revenue accounts
Increases
Decreases
Purpose and limitation of a trial balance
The teacher should guide the learner in explaining the
• purpose of a trial balance.which include:-
A trial balance is used to check the accuracy in the
ledger accounts as to whether the rule of double entry
has been observed or whether there are arithmetical
errors,
limitations of a trial balance explaining the errors that
affect and those that do not affect the agreement of a
trial balance.
In describing and recording transactions relating to the
item stock. These are:
sales account
sales returns account (Return Inwards),
• Purchases account
purchases returns account (Return outwards account).
Classification of ledger accounts
The teacher should involve the leaner in classifying accounts
into personal, private and impersonal giving relevant
examples as follows:
Recording business transactions in the ledger accounts
The teacher should guide the learner in recording business
transactions in various ledger accounts.
